19 Dec 2016Minister Faith Muthambi to present a Humanitarian Award to Dr Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma during the state of the Continent media briefingThe Minister of Communications, Ms Faith Muthambi will on Monday, 19 December present a Humanitarian Award for Leadership to Dr Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma for her sterling role in realizing Agenda 2063. The Award presentation will be done during the State of the Continent Media Briefing to be held in Durban. Dr Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma will address the media for the last time as the Chair of the African Union Commission and give media an opportunity to engage with her as she concludes her four year tenure. Members of the media are invited to witness the Award presentation by Minister Muthambi during the State of the Continent media briefing taking place as follows: Date: Monday, 19 December 2016 Time: 11h00 (media arrives for registration) Venue: Hilton Hotel (Ballroom), Durban NB: Media houses are advised to ensure the punctuality of journalists as the event will be live. Journalists and guests are expected to be seated by 12h15 exactly. For RSVP and interview requests contact: Ms Mmemme Mogotsi Email: mmemme@gcis.gov.za Cell: 072 856 4288Enquiries: Mr Ayanda Holo Contact: 0614880634 Email: holo@gcis.gov.zaIssued by GCIS on behalf of the Department of Communications